                                    Sign up</a></li>
                            <% } %>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </header>

        <div class="hero">
            <div class="box">
                <div class="title">
                    <div class="block"></div>
                    <h1>KFUPM CourseCraft<span></span></h1>
                </div>
                <div class="role">
                    <div class="block"></div>
                    <p>Your ultimate tool for academic planning at KFUPM</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-12">

                    <article>
                        <h2 class="headerText">What is KFUPM CourseCraft?</h2>
                        <p class="paraText">
                            KFUPM CourseCraft is a web application designed to enhance
                            the
                            academic planning and resource management experience for
                            students at
                            King Fahd University of Petroleum and Minerals (KFUPM). This
                            application addresses several issues with the current
                            system, known as
                            the Student Educational Planner (SEP), which students find
                            not
                            user-friendly and difficult to use.
                        </p>
                    </article>

                    <article>
                        <h2 class="headerText">Why KFUPM CourseCraft?</h2>
                        <div class="paraText">
                            <ol>
                                <li>
                                    <strong>Improved User Experience</strong>: Offering
                                    a smoother
                                    user experience for students while planning their
                                    future academic
                                    terms.
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <strong>Centralized Resource Access</strong>
                                    :Combining useful
                                    resources in one place, making it easier for
                                    students to find and
                                    utilize them.
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <strong>Key Requirements</strong>:
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>
                                            <strong>Academic Planning</strong>: Enable
                                            students to develop
                                            and modify their academic plans, search for
                                            courses, and check
                                            for scheduling conflicts and prerequisite
                                            fulfillment.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            <strong>Course Resource Access</strong>:
                                            Centralize access to
                                            course materials and ensure ease of finding
                                            necessary study
                                            materials.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            <strong>Instructor Evaluations</strong>:
                                            Allow students to
                                            provide feedback on instructors, and view
                                            evaluations made by
                                            others.
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            <strong>Administrative Features</strong>:
                                            Provide
                                            administrators with tools to moderate
                                            content, handle
                                            technical issues, and manage the platform.
                                        </li>
                                    </ul>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <strong>Non-functional Requirements</strong>: The
                                    platform aims to
                                    be user-friendly, responsive, secure, capable of
                                    handling a
                                    growing number of users, and accessible from various
                                    devices.
                                </li>
                            </ol>
                        </div>
                    </article>

                    <article>
                        <h2 class="headerText">Schedule</h2>
                        <p class="paraText">
                            In the context of academic planning, a schedule would
                            typically a way
                            to plan and organize of courses over a semester or academic
                            year. This
                            could involve checking for scheduling conflicts.
                        </p>
                    </article>

                    <article>
                        <h2 class="headerText">Resources</h2>
                        <p>
                            Resources in KFUPM CourseCraft primarily include
                            course-related
                            materials. These could be lecture notes, study guides, past
                            exam
                            papers, or any other educational content relevant to the
                            courses
                            offered at KFUPM.
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Functionality for Students</strong>: Students
                                can download
                                available resources for their courses.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Process</strong>: The student, upon logging in
                                and
                                navigating to the resources section, selects the
                                resource they wish
                                to download. The system then initiates the download, and
                                the student
                                receives the downloaded resource.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </article>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>


        <footer class="text-center py-3">
            <p>&copy; 2023 KFUPM CourseCraft</p>
        </footer>
